WSP is currently seeking an Electrical Contract Administrator to join our Buildings Mechanical & Electrical Engineering group, located at our Ottawa office.
Reporting to the Project Manager(s), the incumbent will be responsible for the Contract Administration related to Health Care, Commercial, Residential, construction projects. You will work together with clients, municipalities and contractors on constructability reviews, quality assurance and resolving construction issues.
This is an exciting opportunity with career growth potential targeted to learn the skills necessary towards management and leadership in the Building Division.
A typical day will include….
Oversee and manage the electrical contract administration process on all types and sizes of projects;
Liaise with project stakeholders (building owners, contractors, architects, engineers and management) on an ongoing basis;
Maintain regular communication with clients regarding project status, site issues, project quality and resolve issues as required;
Identify potential risk to project manager and develop potential solutions;
Perform site inspection to review project progress, ensure contractor follow contract documents requirement and quality assurance process, identify systems deficiencies and resolution;
Preparation of monthly payment certificates and progress reports;
Management, tracking and preparations of contemplated change notice, site instructions, responses to Contractor’s RFI’s and clarification requests;
Oversee Change Requests and Claims;
Preparation of Engineering Certifications;
Complete tasks in line with WSP’s safety policies/procedures and legislative requirements;
We’d love to hear from you if you have….
CET or C.Tech designation with 10+ years in Contract Administration and Site Inspection, experience on large projects with specific experience in buildings electrical systems;
Work in a fast-paced environment with minimal direct oversight;
Have strong understanding of the Ontario Building Code, Health Care Standards and building controls, mechanical and electrical systems;
Effectively communicate project issues to project managers and team members in a timely and clear fashion;
Strong English written and verbal communication skills, French would be an asset;
Possess a strong interpersonal style and approach that earns customer trust and builds creditability while getting strong performance of subcontractors and others involved in the fulfillment of a project;
Good attention to detail and accuracy of work;
Experienced in project planning, risk management, cost management, schedule management and constructability review of contract documents and specifications;
Computer skills including word, excel, PDF markup and windows applications;
Valid driver’s license required. This position requires use of personal vehicle in good working order to be used occasionally for business use, for which there is reimbursement.
