As a BI and data integration developer, you will participate in the company’s various BI projects and requests and contribute to its evolution. You will participate across the entire BI platform from integration to visualization.
RESPONSABILITIES
Develop and maintain data extraction, transformation and loading (ETL) solutions with Microsoft SSIS;
Develop and maintain Power BI reports;
Act as an expert in the creation and optimization of SQL queries;
Contribute to the data architecture and the detailed design of the solution;
Maintain the technical documentation of the BI environment, ETL processes and reports;
Collaborate with architects, programmers, business analysts and project managers in the execution of various projects.
QUALIFICATIONS REQUIRED
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent experience;
Minimum 5 years’ experience with Microsoft SQL Server, SSIS, SSRS and SSAS products;
Minimum 3 years’ experience with Microsoft Power BI and DAX language;
Extensive knowledge of SQL language and query optimization;
Very good knowledge of BI principles (Data Vault, DWH decision-making, Cubes, Data Lake);
Focused on problem solving, taking initiative and innovation;
Enjoys working in a collaborative and dynamic environment;
Bilingualism, written and spoken (French and English).
